Section 1:
1 L.D. 105
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
4 Reproduced and distributed under the direction of the Clerk of the House.
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 70, L.D. 105, “An Act to Implement the
10 Recommendations of the Commission Regarding Foreign-trained Physicians Living in
11 Maine to Establish a Sponsorship Program for Internationally Trained Physicians”
12 Amend the bill in section 1 in §12103-B in subsection 2 in the 3rd line (page 1, line 14
13 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "alternative" and inserting the following: 'additional'
14 Amend the bill in section 1 in §12103-B in subsection 3 in the 4th line (page 1, line 21
15 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "practice" the following: 'supervised'
16 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 8 in the first line (page 2, line 1 in L.D.) by
17 striking out the following: "Alternative" and inserting the following: 'Additional'
18 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 8 in the 3rd line (page 2, line 3 in L.D.) by
19 striking out the following: "alternative" and inserting the following: 'additional'
20 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 8 in paragraph A by striking out all of
21 subparagraph (1) (page 2, lines 9 to 14 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
22 '(1) "Internationally trained physician" means a physician who has received a
23 degree of doctor of medicine or its equivalent from a legally chartered medical
24 school outside the United States recognized by the World Federation for Medical
25 Education and the Foundation for Advancement of International Medical
26 Education and Research or their successor organizations; who has been licensed or
27 otherwise authorized to practice medicine in a country other than the United States;
28 and who has practiced medicine for at least 2 years.'
29 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 8 in paragraph A in subparagraph (3) in the
30 last 2 lines (page 2, lines 19 and 20 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "and that provides
31 medical care in a physician shortage area"
32 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 8 in paragraph B in the 2nd line (page 2, line
33 27 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "practice" the following: 'supervised'
Page 1 - 132LR0193(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 70, L.D. 105
1 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 8 in paragraph B in subparagraph (4) in the
2 3rd line (page 2, line 40 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "with" the following:
3 'clinical and'
4 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 8 in paragraph E in the 2nd line (page 3, line
5 16 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "6 years" and inserting the following: 'the same
6 number of years the internationally trained physician practiced supervised medicine
7 pursuant to paragraph B'
8 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 8 by inserting after paragraph E the following:
9 'F. The board may adopt rules as necessary to implement this subsection. Rules
10 adopted pursuant to this paragraph are routine technical rules as defined in Title 5,
11 chapter 375, subchapter 2-A.'
12 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 8 in paragraph F in the 4th line (page 3, line
13 22 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "alternative" and inserting the following:
14 'additional'
15 Amend the bill in section 2 in §3271 in subsection 8 by relettering the paragraphs to
16 read alphabetically.
17 Amend the bill by inserting after section 2 the following:
18 'Sec. 3. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
19 allocations are made.
20 FINANCE AUTHORITY OF MAINE
21 International Medical Graduates Sponsorship Program N493
22 Initiative: Provides ongoing funds to establish 10 positions annually at one or more
23 sponsoring institutions for the employment and training of internationally trained
24 physicians issued a temporary educational license to practice medicine pursuant to the
25 Maine Revised Statutes, Title 32, section 3271, subsection 8.
26 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
27 All Other $2,500,000 $2,500,000
28 __________ __________
29 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $2,500,000 $2,500,000
3206 '
31 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
32 number to read consecutively.
33 SUMMARY
3344 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, makes the following
3355 changes to the bill.
36 1. It changes "alternative license pathway" to "additional license pathway" to reflect
37 current terminology used at the national level.
38 2. It updates the names of the organizations currently responsible for maintaining the
39 directory of world medical schools.
Page 2 - 132LR0193(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 70, L.D. 105
1 3. It extends the time period that an internationally trained physician must have
2 practiced medicine from at least 1 year to at least 2 years.
3 4. It clarifies the time period required for an internationally trained physician to practice
4 under the conditions specified in the bill before applying for a full and unrestricted license.
5 5. It adds language authorizing the Board of Licensure in Medicine to adopt rules.
6 6. It adds an appropriations and allocations section.
77 7. It makes other technical changes.
88 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
99 (See attached)
Page 3 - 132LR0193(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
